The paper discusses the deployment of a publish/subscribe protocol for IoT applications in 5G networks, which involves distributed communication and resource management. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses challenges in protocol design and optimization, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of multiaccess edge computing, which could be relevant to the Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed) sub-category. The paper also discusses the benefits of the pub/sub architecture for IoT applications, which could be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of advanced caching and aggregation functionalities, which could be relevant to the Augmented Reality and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.AR) sub-category.
